HEADWORD: Syllabary
<hw>Syl"la*ba*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A table of
syllables; more especially, a table of the indivisible syllabic symbols
used in certain languages, as the Japanese and Cherokee, instead of
letters.</def> <rj><au>S. W. Williams.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

